## Library Conventions

### Public API

- Define clear public API in index/\_\_init\_\_
- Use barrel exports for clean imports
- Document all public functions and classes
- Mark internal functions with underscore prefix

### Exports

```{{language}}
// Good: explicit exports
export { ComponentA, ComponentB } from './components';
export type { ConfigOptions } from './types';

// Bad: export everything
export * from './internal';
```

### Documentation

- MUST document all public API with JSDoc/docstrings
- MUST include usage examples in documentation
- MUST maintain README with quick start guide
- SHOULD include API reference documentation

## Versioning

### Semantic Versioning

| Change | Version |
|--------|---------|
| Breaking change | Major (X.0.0) |
| New feature | Minor (0.X.0) |
| Bug fix | Patch (0.0.X) |

### Release Process

1. Update version in package.json/pyproject.toml
2. Update CHANGELOG.md
3. Commit: `chore: release vX.Y.Z`
4. Tag: `git tag vX.Y.Z`
5. Push with tags
6. Publish to registry

## Compatibility

- Document supported versions of runtime/language
- Test against multiple versions in CI
- Minimize dependencies
- Document peer dependencies clearly
